Here is the full insights data:
{
  "project_areas": {
    "areas": [
      {
        "name": "OmegA Web App Development & Deployment",
        "session_count": 7,
        "description": "Building and deploying the OmegA full-stack application on Vercel with Next.js/TypeScript frontend, Neon database backend, and voice interface. Claude Code handled Tailwind/CSP fixes, database ingestion, architecture blueprints, build verification, and porting a Python stack to TypeScript. This was the core project area with significant multi-file editing and debugging."
      },
      {
        "name": "Voice Service & API Integration Debugging",
        "session_count": 4,
        "description": "Debugging voice service functionality including  API key issues, model name mismatches, and Python venv/pip problems for a local voice loop. Claude Code was used extensively for iterative diagnosis and fix-retry cycles, though progress was often hampered by external API rate limits and configuration complexity."
      },
      {
        "name": "System Maintenance & Environment Configuration",
        "session_count": 5,
        "description": "Terminal configuration fixes, disk cleanup freeing ~45GB, CLAUDE.md creation, NVM file repairs, codex CLI debugging, and MCP server setup. Claude Code traced shell injection issues, managed file deletions with permission handling, built a TypeScript MCP server, and mined conversation history for notable quotes."
      },
      {
        "name": "Vercel & Deployment Infrastructure",
        "session_count": 3,
        "description": "Fixing DATABASE_URL configuration, resolving auth walls, managing Vercel project deployments, and Alexa skill deployment scripting. Claude Code diagnosed deployment blockers, created CLI deploy scripts when browser automation failed, and audited existing Vercel projects."
      },
      {
        "name": "Rate Limit & Access Interruptions",
        "session_count": 6,
        "description": "Multiple sessions were lost or severely degraded due to API rate limits, credit balance errors, and usage caps. These interruptions frequently broke workflow continuity, forced context recovery in subsequent sessions, and prevented subagent-based parallel task execution."
      }
    ]
  },
